The paper deals with the design of efficient checkers for testing the reliability of massive data structures, specifically priority queues. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The use of timestamps and passes on the sequence of operations suggests a connection to communication complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The focus on minimizing memory space and number of passes suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG), where efficient use of resources is a key concern.
